Subject: Wesphalia camp out and cruise[Texas]

Saturdayy started out overcast but very pleasant, it warmed up to about 80 and sun shine ,perfect weather for a camp out and cruise.20 type 2"s ,several real nice beetles and 50+ vw people joined in all the festivities . we started out with a fried turky dinner and all the trimmings. afterwards we had the raffle, with some great prizes from,rocky mountain motor works, vintage motor werks,real source, patties parts palace, go westie,wolfgang international,koch,s,califoria import parts, and a lot of stuff donated by sharon chamberlain.i belive every one got a prize, we then lined up and cruised ti wesphalia tx. stopped to take some pictures and then cruised  back twords lake belton to the country kitchen restraunt for supper. then back to the park,a norther blew in sunday morning and made the sleep that more enjoyable. sunday morning ted from kileen cooked breakfast for everyone, some parts swapping and much story telling was had before everyone headed their separate ways.20 campers is small by the arch and jarome standards but for around here it was pretty good. we had a great family atmosephere with lots of bike ridind and roller bladeing. special thanx to steve and sharon for all their hard work and dedication to the vw brand also to dennis holbrook, and larry parrot for some great fried turky, it was my first campout but it won't be my last, thanks to everyone for coming ,they came from ,houston,san an tonio,ft.worth,dallas, est texas, abilen and plases inbetween.one good thing that came out of this camp out is that the monky is off my back for running out of gas at an event, i won't mention any names.


